==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shove
<hw>Shove</hw> <pr>(sh⟦ucr⟧v)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Shoved</conjf> <pr>(sh⟦ucr⟧vd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Shoving</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>shoven</ets>, AS. <ets>scofian</ets>, fr. <ets>sc⟦umac⟧fan</ets>;
akin to OFries. <ets>sk⟦umac⟧va</ets>, D. <ets>schuiven</ets>, G.
<ets>schieben</ets>, OHG. <ets>scioban</ets>, Icel.
<ets>sk⟦umac⟧fa</ets>, <ets>sk⟦ymac⟧fa</ets>, Sw. <ets>skuffa</ets>,
Dan. <ets>skuffe</ets>, Goth. af<ets>skiuban</ets> to put away, cast
away; cf. Skr. <ets>kshubh</ets> to become agitated, to quake, Lith.
<ets>skubrus</ets> quick, <ets>skubinti</ets> to hasten. ⟦root⟧160. Cf.
<er>Sheaf</er> a bundle of stalks, <er>Scoop</er>,
<er>Scuffle</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To drive along by the direct
and continuous application of strength; to push; especially, to push (a
body) so as to make it move along the surface of another body; <as>as,
to <ex>shove</ex> a boat on the water; to <ex>shove</ex> a table across
the floor.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To push along, aside, or away, in a careless or rude
manner; to jostle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And <qex>shove</qex> away the worthy bidden guest.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He used to <qex>shove</qex> and elbow his fellow servants.</q>
<rj><qau>Arbuthnot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shove</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Shove
<hw>Shove</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To push or drive
forward; to move onward by pushing or jostling.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To move off or along by an act pushing, as with an
oar a pole used by one in a boat; sometimes with
<xex>off</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He grasped the oar,⟦br⟧
eceived his guests on board, and <qex>shoved</qex> from shore.</q>
<rj><qau>Garth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shove</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Shove
<hw>Shove</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of shoving; a
forcible push.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I rested . . . and then gave the boat another
<qex>shove</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Thrust</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shove</ent>⟦br⟧

